The paper discusses the calculation of receptive fields, effective receptive fields, and projective fields in convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization of performance, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical calculations and analysis, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
